Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [telegram] <Regnar> Seeds are the 12-24 words you are shown when you create a wallet, they are basically your private keys, NEVER share them. They can be used in any lite wallet to access your funds. The pin and passwords you see on Agama are like locks on your phone to prevent someone from opening the apps. They don't do anything except lock your app. So a pin from mobile doesn't do anything for the desktop wallet and vice versa, but the seed, because it's your keys, will give you access

Content:
[telegram] <Regnar> üëç just remember, store your seed somewhere safe, don't leave it screenshot on your phone or something (people do it) those are your keys and whoever has those owns your coins.
The pin, password, and wallet name have nothing to do with the blockchain or your funds. They are only to lock the app so someone who steals your phone can't gain access. 
Think about your phone lockscreen passcode. That protects the contents in your phone. Those pin/password protect the contents in your wallet (your seed). So a phone pin won't unlock a wallet on your computer.
